reer total\n!586||155||87||27||50||10||28||6||781||198\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list England's goal tally first.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sporting-heroes.net/football/england/john-barnes-7615/international-football-caps-for-england_a10996/ |title=John Barnes international caps and goals |publisher=Sporting-heroes.net |date= |accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref>''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Result !! Competition !! Scored\n|-\n| 1 || 10 June 1984 || [[Maracan\u00e3 Stadium]], [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil || {{fb|BRA}} || 2\u20130 || Friendly || 1\n|-\n| 2, 3 || 14 November 1984 || [[BJK \u0130n\u00f6n\u00fc Stadium|Besiktas Inonu Stadium]], [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]] || {{fb|TUR}} || 8\u20130 || [[1986 FIFA World Cup qualification|1986 World Cup qualifier]] || 2\n|-\n| 4, 5 || 14 October 1987 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|TUR}} || 8\u20130 || [[UEFA Euro 1988 qualifying|Euro 1988 qualifier]] || 2\n|-\n| 6 || 11 November 1987 || [[Red Star Stadium]], [[Belgrade]], [[Yugoslavia]] || {{fb|YUG}} || 4\u20131 || [[UEFA Euro 1988 qualifying|Euro 1988 qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 7 || 8 February 1989 || [[Olympic Stadium (Athens)|Olympic Stadium]], [[Athens]], [[Greece]] || {{fb|GRE}} || 2\u20131 || Friendly || 1\n|-\n| 8 || 8 March 1989 || [[Qemal Stafa Stadium]], [[Tirana]], [[Albania]] || {{fb|ALB}} || 2-0 || [[1990 FIFA World Cup qualification|1990 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 9 || 3 June 1989 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|POL}} || 3\u20130 || [[1990 FIFA World Cup qualification|1990 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 10 || 22 May 1990 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|URU}} || 1-2 || Friendly || 1\n|-\n| 11 || 28 April 1993 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|NED}} || 2\u20132 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|1994 World Cup qualifi